name: Pro Series - 55mm – Pedro Barros Signature Pro Wheel 98a
description:
Pro Series - 55mm – Pedro Barros

This long awaited pro signature wheel is merely an extention of Pedro's skating. It's our first colored swirl wheel. Just like Bastien's wheel, it's also made with the same original 98A blend. The DCR core is the same as the main color in the urethane swirl. The dimensions are to his specs as well, 33mm wide and a 20mm riding surface dressed up with the "V-shape" This wheel helped him SWEEP and go undefeated in the 2012 World bowl Series, first time in bowl skating history!

4-pack
55mm | 98A
Color: swirl orange

name: Pro Series - 58mm – Bucky Lasek Signature Pro Wheel 96a
description:
Pro Series - 58mm – Bucky Lasek

Made with the same 96A soft blend formula, the new non exposed DCR core, and the new "V" shape, this wheel is designed for high performance. With no running grooves on the riding surface and with symmetrical dimensions that compliment his style of riding, Bucky's new signature pro wheel is the new favorite for all our bowl and vert skaters. The bigger riding surface along with the softer urethane blend provides the grip and speed that most want out of a wheel. It's a perfect combination.

4-pack
58mm | 96A, RS20
Color: white

name: Ben Schroeder Broken T After
description: Ben Schroeder broke his leg about 9 months ago and it ended up healing completely jacked. He recently went to Denmark to build a Skatepark, and while he was there he was able to get the intense surgery needed to get his leg back to normal. He is now stuck there for 4 months while under going treatment to heal his leg. All proceeds from this shirt will go directly to Ben to help cover his expenses while he is in Denmark. Thanks for your support! Never Surrender!
